WEBVTT

00:06.979 --> 00:08.799
Previously, on "smash".

00:09.945 --> 00:12.045
- What's that?
- Nothing.

00:14.113 --> 00:16.513
You have lost control of the rehearsal
room.

00:16.559 --> 00:17.959
This one.

00:18.020 --> 00:19.840
Boston, next week.

00:22.595 --> 00:24.488
He loosing control of her,
and that's scarring.

00:24.489 --> 00:25.395
I think you've got it.

00:25.598 --> 00:27.998
- You should have that song.
- I'm work on.

00:28.014 --> 00:30.114
I was foolish, I've made mistakes.

00:32.229 --> 00:35.730
Stop messing up with you're understood,
in fact stop messing about with me.

00:36.156 --> 00:37.976
Smash
s01 ep 13 - Tech

00:38.057 --> 00:41.557
sync and corrected by dr.Jackson
for www.Addic7ed.Com

00:47.603 --> 00:53.058
both: ♪ in Philly,
Boston, or Baltimo' ♪

00:53.109 --> 00:56.695
- I like that.
- I like you.

00:56.729 --> 00:59.564
Both: ♪ a chance
for stage folks ♪

00:59.615 --> 01:02.651
♪ To say hello

01:02.685 --> 01:06.488
- [plays piano dramatically]
- [Laughs]

01:06.522 --> 01:09.491
Both: ♪ another op'nin'

01:09.525 --> 01:14.162
♪ of another

01:14.196 --> 01:15.580
take it, baby.

01:15.631 --> 01:20.368
♪ Show

01:21.704 --> 01:23.972
over here!
[Clamoring]

01:25.641 --> 01:31.847
♪ Another job
that you hope at last ♪

01:31.881 --> 01:38.186
♪ Will make your future
forget your past ♪

01:38.221 --> 01:43.608
♪ Another pain
where the ulcers grow ♪

01:43.659 --> 01:47.913
♪ Another op'nin'
of another show ♪

01:47.947 --> 01:50.282
♪ Four weeks
you rehearse and rehearse ♪

01:50.316 --> 01:54.202
♪ Three weeks
and it couldn't be worse ♪

01:54.236 --> 01:57.372
♪ One week
will it ever be right? ♪

01:57.406 --> 02:00.625
♪ Then out of the hat

02:00.660 --> 02:03.645
♪ out of the hat

02:03.679 --> 02:10.101
♪ it's that big first night

02:10.136 --> 02:13.588
♪ the overture
is about to start ♪

02:13.623 --> 02:16.558
[Opening notes of
<i>let me be your star</i> playing]

02:16.592 --> 02:18.092
♪ You cross your fingers

02:18.110 --> 02:22.931
♪ and hold your heart

02:22.949 --> 02:29.604
♪ it's curtain time
and away we go ♪

02:29.639 --> 02:32.490
♪ Another op'nin'

02:32.542 --> 02:35.126
♪ another op'nin

02:35.161 --> 02:37.161
♪ of another

02:42.284 --> 02:43.468
♪ show

02:43.502 --> 02:48.456
let's see that cue.

02:48.474 --> 02:53.345
Oh, bloody hell!

02:55.000 --> 03:01.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:23.068 --> 03:24.702
[Door opens]

03:34.746 --> 03:37.998
[Sighs]

03:58.353 --> 04:00.971
- Hi.
- Oh, hi.

04:01.022 --> 04:03.040
Thank you.

04:03.074 --> 04:04.892
Still working
on that transition?

04:04.926 --> 04:06.310
[Sighs]
Yeah.

04:06.344 --> 04:07.711
I've been looking
at this for so long,

04:07.746 --> 04:09.463
I can't even
see it any more.

04:09.497 --> 04:12.166
It's these platforms.

04:12.200 --> 04:14.952
No, it's a choreography
problem, not a set problem.

04:14.986 --> 04:16.570
If you just
move the boys downstage

04:16.603 --> 04:18.288
during the U.S.O. number...

04:18.322 --> 04:21.809
Yeah, that would sort out
the spill from this light here.

04:21.843 --> 04:25.229
- That's not bad.
- I am a woman of many talents.

04:25.263 --> 04:28.549
And that is
why I love you.

04:36.891 --> 04:42.846
[Orchestra tuning up]

04:52.516 --> 04:55.985
[Cell phone ringing]

05:00.991 --> 05:03.243
Ugh, I'm sorry.

05:06.080 --> 05:07.363
Dev?

05:07.414 --> 05:09.032
Dev.

05:09.083 --> 05:10.950
I was thinking of you.

05:10.984 --> 05:12.785
Aw, that's so sweet.

05:12.819 --> 05:15.288
But you just
woke up my roommate.

05:15.322 --> 05:17.123
It's almost 9:00.

05:17.157 --> 05:19.175
We're doing
10 out of 12s,

05:19.210 --> 05:21.628
which means we work
from 10:00 to 10:00, so...

05:21.662 --> 05:23.513
Then we're all wound up.
We go out.

05:23.547 --> 05:25.698
Listen, I was thinking
I'd come up this weekend.

05:25.733 --> 05:28.618
That's great.

05:28.652 --> 05:31.321
Great, okay, except...
Okay, well, I have a roommate.

05:31.355 --> 05:32.622
Is that a problem?

05:32.656 --> 05:34.040
I just don't want you
to come up

05:34.074 --> 05:35.458
and pay for an extra room,

05:35.492 --> 05:36.659
and then not even
have time to see you.

05:36.694 --> 05:38.044
I'll see you
at the theater.

05:38.078 --> 05:40.713
[Knock at door]
Karen, I need to pee.

05:40.748 --> 05:43.032
You know what,
can I call you back?

05:43.067 --> 05:44.534
I have
to call you back, okay?

05:44.568 --> 05:47.770
- Love you. Bye.
- Really?

05:54.396 --> 05:56.080
This desk
is way too heavy.

05:56.115 --> 05:58.549
We're gonna need
smart casters.

05:58.567 --> 06:00.551
Okay.

06:00.569 --> 06:02.553
Oh, thought
you were Linda.

06:02.588 --> 06:04.055
Good morning to you, too.

06:04.073 --> 06:05.389
Listen, I have
a really good idea

06:05.407 --> 06:08.109
for a song
for Karen and Ivy.

06:08.160 --> 06:10.445
We agreed the shadow selves
weren't gonna sing, remember?

06:10.496 --> 06:12.280
This is different,
and it's already finished.

06:12.331 --> 06:13.698
It's a number we wrote
for <i>Heaven on earth</i>

06:13.732 --> 06:14.732
that got cut
at the last minute.

06:14.750 --> 06:16.417
It's a great number.

06:16.452 --> 06:19.087
I'm not putting in
a new song during Tech, Tom.

06:19.121 --> 06:23.174
Could you at least try
to be open?

06:25.243 --> 06:26.260
Why?

06:26.295 --> 06:28.796
[Exhales]
Ted, hey.

06:28.847 --> 06:30.414
You're not called
for another hour, are you?

06:30.432 --> 06:32.083
I have to talk
to you... both.

06:32.101 --> 06:33.718
- Everything okay?
- Great.

06:33.752 --> 06:36.888
Well, great for me.
I got a pilot.

06:36.922 --> 06:38.473
Ooh, a pilot, great.

06:38.507 --> 06:40.224
It starts shooting
next week in Las Vegas,

06:40.258 --> 06:41.476
so... I kind of
can't play DiMaggio.

06:41.527 --> 06:43.111
Hang on.

06:43.145 --> 06:44.595
I've got to catch a plane
in, like, an hour.

06:44.613 --> 06:46.230
- I'm sorry.
- Hang on!

06:46.264 --> 06:47.598
The show is great.

06:47.616 --> 06:48.900
I'm sorry.

06:48.934 --> 06:52.120
Okay, we have to not panic.

06:52.154 --> 06:54.405
Yeah, I'm not panicking.
Linda!

06:54.439 --> 06:56.107
- Yes?
- Now, get me

06:56.125 --> 06:57.575
Michael Swift's availability,
and get me Eileen.

06:57.609 --> 06:59.160
- Okay.
- Derek, there's something

06:59.211 --> 07:00.912
you need to know.

07:00.946 --> 07:02.897
Michael and Julia?
Yeah, yeah, I'm not an idiot.

07:02.931 --> 07:04.449
I just mind my own business.

07:04.483 --> 07:09.087
Call her and tell her, Tom.
That's your job.

07:09.121 --> 07:11.472
[As Marilyn]
"Real diamonds.

07:11.507 --> 07:15.510
They must be worth
their weight in gold."

07:15.561 --> 07:18.346
- That wig looks good on you.
- Thanks.

07:18.397 --> 07:20.098
Probably looks better
on you than on me.

07:20.132 --> 07:21.632
No, it doesn't.

07:21.650 --> 07:24.602
Stop it, girls.
You're both beautiful.

07:24.636 --> 07:27.105
- You're paid to say that.
- No, I'm not.

07:27.139 --> 07:29.824
Out.

07:29.858 --> 07:31.976
You okay?

07:31.994 --> 07:36.114
Mm, okay.

07:36.148 --> 07:37.832
I'm nervous.

07:37.866 --> 07:39.817
You get nervous?
You're Rebecca Duvall.

07:39.835 --> 07:42.653
[Chuckles]
Yeah.

07:42.671 --> 07:44.989
When I was your age,
I thought I'd reach this plateau

07:45.007 --> 07:47.141
and fear would stop.

07:47.176 --> 07:49.644
I'd finally stop worrying.

07:49.678 --> 07:51.996
But it never does.

07:52.031 --> 07:55.216
It never goes away.

07:55.267 --> 07:59.020
- Great.
- Yeah.

07:59.054 --> 08:00.855
[Whispers]
Sorry.

08:05.778 --> 08:06.861
- I can do this.
- Honey...

08:06.895 --> 08:08.312
- Now?
- Yes.

08:08.346 --> 08:09.697
Okay.

08:09.732 --> 08:13.517
- You really can't do it.
- Really?

08:13.535 --> 08:19.240
[Laughs triumphantly]
You did it.

08:19.291 --> 08:21.375
Okay.
It's been over a week.

08:21.410 --> 08:24.262
Are we ready
to call it official?

08:24.296 --> 08:25.246
[Phone rings]
Oh.

08:25.280 --> 08:27.482
Sorry.

08:27.516 --> 08:28.833
Tom?

08:28.867 --> 08:31.702
Julia...
I have some news.

08:31.720 --> 08:32.703
- Everybody, say hi.
- Hey.

08:32.721 --> 08:34.672
Hi, Tom.

08:34.706 --> 08:37.875
- Oh, um, is that...
- Yes.

08:37.893 --> 08:40.711
Frank and Leo.
Frank moved back in a week ago.

08:40.729 --> 08:44.097
It's a little... we're still...
But he's here,

08:44.149 --> 08:46.434
and it's, uh...
It's going well, actually.

08:46.485 --> 08:48.936
I think it's going well.

08:48.987 --> 08:50.688
- That's great.
- I know, right?

08:50.722 --> 08:52.757
You don't need me yet,
right?

08:52.791 --> 08:56.060
Because it would be so great
if I could just stay home

08:56.078 --> 08:58.112
for just
a little bit longer.

08:58.163 --> 09:01.415
No, no, you know,
it's Tech.

09:01.450 --> 09:05.052
- How's it going?
- Um...

09:05.087 --> 09:07.588
The desk for the mambo number
is too heavy.

09:07.623 --> 09:09.740
If we want to keep
the choreography,

09:09.775 --> 09:12.576
we're gonna have
to use smart casters.

09:12.594 --> 09:14.045
That it?

09:14.079 --> 09:16.614
[Sighs]
Just keeping you in the loop.

09:16.648 --> 09:17.882
Okay.

09:17.916 --> 09:20.251
[Background chatter]

09:20.269 --> 09:24.722
How'd it go?
Did you tell her?

09:24.756 --> 09:27.091
Oh, it's called
a spine, Tom.

09:27.109 --> 09:29.894
I'm going to go
into New York today.

09:29.928 --> 09:33.731
- I'm going to talk to her.
- See you later.

09:33.765 --> 09:35.366
Pitiful.

09:37.286 --> 09:38.653
Bring it in.

09:38.704 --> 09:40.271
[Piano: <i>History is made</i>
<i>at night]</i>

09:40.289 --> 09:43.124
Okay... and stop.

09:43.158 --> 09:44.959
He said "I love you"?

09:44.993 --> 09:47.611
It was a shred offhand,
but he definitely said it.

09:47.629 --> 09:49.130
You got any plans
for Derek's birthday tomorrow?

09:49.164 --> 09:50.614
We're just going
to go out for dinner.

09:50.632 --> 09:52.466
- Got a nice dress?
- A very nice dress.

09:52.501 --> 09:55.503
Excuse me, did you say it was
Derek's birthday tomorrow?

09:55.554 --> 09:57.955
Okay, we'll be taking it
from the top, please.

09:57.973 --> 10:00.624
Places, everyone.

10:07.816 --> 10:09.466
Where's Ted?

10:09.484 --> 10:11.602
- He got a pilot.
- He got a what?

10:11.636 --> 10:12.987
Pilot?

10:13.021 --> 10:15.156
No one saw fit
to tell me

10:15.190 --> 10:16.974
that my leading man
has left the show?

10:16.992 --> 10:18.642
Yeah, we just didn't
want to worry you.

10:18.660 --> 10:20.528
Worry me?
Half my scenes are with Ted.

10:20.579 --> 10:22.163
We preview in two days,

10:22.197 --> 10:24.982
and you dump this on me
in front of the cast?

10:25.000 --> 10:26.483
I need a minute.

10:26.501 --> 10:28.202
- Rebecca!
- Derek, I don't understand!

10:28.253 --> 10:30.821
- Rebecca, wait.
- You don't help me.

10:30.839 --> 10:32.707
You don't talk to me.

10:32.758 --> 10:36.160
Because I don't
have time, okay?

10:36.178 --> 10:38.629
Look, it is Tech.
It will make you crazy.

10:38.663 --> 10:40.047
It's all about the set
and the lights.

10:40.098 --> 10:42.550
That's what it is,
all right?

10:42.601 --> 10:44.168
Listen to me.

10:44.186 --> 10:45.803
You go to wardrobe.

10:45.837 --> 10:47.555
There's a hundred costumes
that need fitting, okay?

10:47.606 --> 10:50.558
And we'll find
a better DiMaggio, I promise.

10:50.609 --> 10:55.229
Okay? Good.

10:55.280 --> 10:58.816
[Sighs]
Ivy.

10:58.850 --> 11:00.985
Downstage center, please,
with Dennis.

11:01.019 --> 11:02.853
Quickly.

11:02.871 --> 11:04.238
Okay, from the top.

11:04.289 --> 11:07.541
[Playing
<i>History is made at night]</i>

11:07.576 --> 11:11.045
All:
♪ missing the whole story

11:11.079 --> 11:13.698
♪

11:13.732 --> 11:17.168
♪ 'Cause history
is made at night ♪

11:17.202 --> 11:18.920
♪ So close the books

11:18.971 --> 11:22.206
♪ turn off the light
and listen ♪

11:22.224 --> 11:23.874
Hold.

11:23.892 --> 11:26.210
I need you to fade those out
faster, please, Don.

11:26.245 --> 11:27.845
You got it.

11:27.879 --> 11:31.882
Okay, refocus on me here,
please, the VL-6.

11:31.900 --> 11:35.686
- That good?
- Finally, the hot spot.

11:35.720 --> 11:36.887
Oh, I feel it.

11:36.905 --> 11:39.723
What would I do
without you?

11:42.444 --> 11:44.895
Look, I know that
everybody thinks I'm a joke.

11:44.913 --> 11:47.865
Oh, stop it.
No, they don't.

11:47.899 --> 11:50.418
Derek, you're having
other people standing in for me.

11:50.452 --> 11:53.237
You don't even tell me
about losing my leading man.

11:53.255 --> 11:56.540
I am just trying to make
an already difficult situation...

11:56.574 --> 11:59.110
Stop trying.

11:59.144 --> 12:01.929
What are we gonna do here?

12:03.932 --> 12:06.651
[Sighs]
Okay.

12:06.685 --> 12:09.153
[Clicks tongue]

12:09.187 --> 12:13.641
You know, Marilyn was
always afraid of being a joke.

12:13.675 --> 12:17.094
Well, that feeling
of not being authentic,

12:17.129 --> 12:21.399
having something to prove...

12:21.433 --> 12:23.033
Use it.

12:28.490 --> 12:31.575
Good.

12:31.610 --> 12:34.161
Oh, and if I were you...

12:34.212 --> 12:37.164
I'd think about using
your star power.

12:37.199 --> 12:39.800
Don't throw it around,
though.

12:39.835 --> 12:44.105
Revel in it.
Find the joy in it.

12:44.139 --> 12:46.607
It's your escape
from the terror.

12:46.641 --> 12:50.177
Okay.

12:50.212 --> 12:55.683
[Derek speaking indistinctly]

12:55.734 --> 12:57.852
Uh, that's usually
my thing.

12:57.903 --> 12:59.937
What?
Oh, I was just...

12:59.971 --> 13:01.605
It's okay.

13:01.639 --> 13:05.142
There's nothing going on
between Derek and Rebecca.

13:07.913 --> 13:09.613
- Everything okay?
- Yeah.

13:09.647 --> 13:11.782
Just wondering if we're
still on for dinner tonight.

13:11.816 --> 13:14.651
Yeah, absolutely.

13:16.755 --> 13:18.456
You'd tell me, right?

13:18.490 --> 13:20.007
I will keep
an eye on it for you.

13:20.042 --> 13:24.512
- Thanks, Ellis.
- For you, anything.

13:27.499 --> 13:29.383
[Whispers]
Revel in it.

13:32.472 --> 13:33.872
It's so weird.

13:33.882 --> 13:35.652
Dev is the love of my
life, but seriously,

13:35.653 --> 13:37.216
I so don't want to see him right now.

13:37.234 --> 13:39.051
No civilians during Tech.

13:39.070 --> 13:40.603
We're in the middle of a war.
They don't get it.

13:40.654 --> 13:42.221
He doesn't.

13:42.239 --> 13:44.223
I moved to New York
with my college boyfriend.

13:44.241 --> 13:45.525
Didn't end well.

13:45.559 --> 13:47.393
We were throwing things
at each other.

13:47.411 --> 13:49.061
- Really?
- Mm-hmm.

13:49.080 --> 13:51.915
Places please, company.
Places.

13:54.068 --> 13:55.952
[Knock at door]

14:00.240 --> 14:01.458
I heard you were sick.

14:01.509 --> 14:02.759
Well, not sick, no.

14:02.793 --> 14:04.427
Um... using my sick days.

14:04.462 --> 14:05.912
I've been
so marginalized,

14:05.930 --> 14:08.898
there's no reason
for me to go in.

14:08.933 --> 14:10.767
You bring bourbon
to sick people?

14:10.801 --> 14:11.968
Oh, yeah,
you'd be surprised

14:12.019 --> 14:13.470
how much better
it makes you feel,

14:13.521 --> 14:17.490
whatever it is
that ails you.

14:17.525 --> 14:20.860
Come on in.

14:24.982 --> 14:27.283
[Knocks at door]
Hey.

14:27.318 --> 14:30.487
I heard from Tom this morning
how well things are going.

14:30.538 --> 14:33.156
Derek staged the new number
for the ensemble.

14:33.207 --> 14:34.491
Things must be
going well

14:34.542 --> 14:36.793
if you have time
to run into New York.

14:36.827 --> 14:38.962
I'm just gonna say it.

14:38.996 --> 14:40.897
Ted's got a pilot.

14:40.931 --> 14:44.667
We have to bring back
Michael Swift.

14:44.702 --> 14:47.237
- Eileen...
- I wish we had a choice.

14:47.271 --> 14:49.772
Our first preview
is on Thursday.

14:49.807 --> 14:51.090
He knows the part...

14:51.124 --> 14:53.143
No, we have
to get someone else.

14:53.177 --> 14:55.461
We can call Zachary,

14:55.479 --> 14:57.597
Corey Harris,
Matthew Tompkins...

14:57.631 --> 14:59.616
Any one of them could
pick this up by then.

14:59.650 --> 15:02.435
- We don't know that.
- You could at least try.

15:02.470 --> 15:05.522
You have no idea
what this did to me.

15:05.573 --> 15:07.490
Eileen, I nearly
lost my family.

15:07.525 --> 15:09.108
Things are still fragile.

15:09.142 --> 15:11.327
Julia, you can take
some time off.

15:11.362 --> 15:13.329
We'll bring him in
without you.

15:13.364 --> 15:15.048
You are not hearing me.

15:15.082 --> 15:16.332
There's too much
at stake, Julia.

15:16.367 --> 15:17.817
I'm aware!

15:17.835 --> 15:19.502
And I'm not going
to sacrifice my family,

15:19.537 --> 15:21.321
my life,
for the theater any more.

15:21.355 --> 15:22.772
Do you hear me?
That's done.

15:22.806 --> 15:24.791
You are taking this
far too personally.

15:24.825 --> 15:28.294
No. Forget it.

15:28.328 --> 15:29.996
Michael
is not coming back,

15:30.014 --> 15:31.297
and that's it.

15:31.331 --> 15:32.465
- End of discussion.
- Julia.

15:32.499 --> 15:35.401
- End of discussion.
- Julia!

15:39.506 --> 15:41.858
It's just what happened.

15:41.892 --> 15:44.060
They were protecting each other,
and you had to go.

15:44.111 --> 15:46.896
- You can't take it to heart.
- Yeah, great.

15:46.947 --> 15:48.848
You're an amazing talent.

15:48.866 --> 15:50.316
You'll bounce back
so quickly,

15:50.350 --> 15:52.235
you'll look back at this
and laugh.

15:52.286 --> 15:55.187
[Laughs]

15:55.206 --> 15:57.073
You're really
good to me.

15:57.124 --> 16:00.359
I try to be.

16:00.377 --> 16:02.328
To my plummeting career.

16:02.362 --> 16:04.881
- To rock bottom.
- Good place.

16:04.915 --> 16:07.584
[Laughs]

16:42.336 --> 16:43.536
I'm sorry,
I can't.

16:43.570 --> 16:46.739
Feels to me
like you can.

16:46.774 --> 16:49.241
I really can't, R.J.
I'm sorry.

16:50.243 --> 16:53.579
I'm sorry.

16:53.597 --> 16:55.414
I'm sorry.

17:00.004 --> 17:01.604
Yeah, I'm waiting, don.

17:01.639 --> 17:03.806
Sometime before the seasons
change would be nice.

17:03.857 --> 17:05.141
Whatcha doing?

17:05.192 --> 17:08.111
Waiting to see Derek
have a stroke.

17:08.145 --> 17:10.445
Oh, my God, don,
are you joking?

17:10.481 --> 17:12.565
If you cross-fade to this
out of a bright yellow wash,

17:12.598 --> 17:14.651
everyone's going to think
they've gone blind!

17:14.702 --> 17:16.569
Excuse me, Derek,
a word.

17:16.603 --> 17:18.488
How about "no"?
That's a word.

17:18.539 --> 17:19.821
Rebecca likes the gloves.

17:19.873 --> 17:22.575
- Really?
- She loves them.

17:22.608 --> 17:24.911
We'll need more time.

17:24.944 --> 17:28.581
Let's try and have a straight
blackout, please... now.

17:28.616 --> 17:30.633
They can't foist this
on us, Tom.

17:30.668 --> 17:32.085
Just tell them no way.

17:32.119 --> 17:33.753
- Okay.
- Don't placate me.

17:33.787 --> 17:35.505
I can hear it
in your voice.

17:35.556 --> 17:38.091
I'm not gonna lie to you.
The clock is ticking here.

17:38.125 --> 17:40.810
Tom, you've seen actors
come in the night before

17:40.844 --> 17:43.012
- and be great.
- We're making some calls.

17:43.063 --> 17:45.181
Okay, whatever you do,
you cannot cave.

17:45.232 --> 17:47.466
You tell her that Michael's
gonna be here when she arrives,

17:47.484 --> 17:50.103
- whether she likes it or not.
- Yes, sure.

17:50.137 --> 17:53.690
I'll handle Rebecca.
You handle Julia.

17:53.741 --> 17:57.327
- Everything okay?
- Fine.

17:57.361 --> 18:00.279
No, not fine.

18:00.313 --> 18:02.782
- What is it?
- [Sighs]

18:02.816 --> 18:05.702
The actor playing Joe DiMaggio
quit the show,

18:05.736 --> 18:08.037
and they want to bring
Michael Swift back.

18:08.072 --> 18:10.056
- No.
- That's what I told them.

18:10.090 --> 18:11.424
I told them no.

18:20.517 --> 18:22.335
Should I not
have told you?

18:22.369 --> 18:24.137
I don't want
to lie to you.

18:24.171 --> 18:25.805
I don't want to lie
to you ever again.

18:25.839 --> 18:30.243
No, that's good.
It's good.

18:30.277 --> 18:31.861
I-I just...

18:35.199 --> 18:37.450
I said no.

18:46.377 --> 18:50.246
[Door opens and closes]

18:55.368 --> 18:57.170
- Okay, what did she say?
- She's getting there.

18:57.204 --> 18:58.871
Well, she needs
to be there now.

18:58.889 --> 19:00.723
By the way,
I'm going to need

19:00.758 --> 19:02.675
a little bit of extra music
for the lead-in to <i>History.</i>

19:02.709 --> 19:05.845
- Uh, what for?
- We have a costume issue.

19:05.879 --> 19:07.847
So talk
to the costume designer.

19:07.881 --> 19:09.882
Tom, Rebecca is
a house of cards right now.

19:09.900 --> 19:11.768
If she needs a costume,
we're going to give it to her.

19:11.802 --> 19:13.552
Okay, but intro music
into <i>History</i>

19:13.570 --> 19:15.738
is kind of
a terrible idea.

19:15.773 --> 19:18.574
Just come up
with something please.

19:18.609 --> 19:20.226
Why?

19:20.260 --> 19:24.414
Okay, do you want me
to beg?

19:24.448 --> 19:26.282
Well, this is me begging.

19:26.333 --> 19:28.234
Give me the song
for Ivy and Karen.

19:28.252 --> 19:31.087
Talk to Josh.

19:31.121 --> 19:34.040
We're at places for
<i>History is made at night.</i>

19:34.074 --> 19:35.758
History is made
at night...

19:35.793 --> 19:37.543
And in the morning
and at lunchtime

19:37.577 --> 19:39.345
and during cocktail hour.

19:41.248 --> 19:42.482
Oh... Don!

19:42.516 --> 19:43.800
Linda, Don,
what cue is this?

19:43.851 --> 19:46.335
Oh, come on, people.

19:49.189 --> 19:51.641
Oh, for God's sake.

19:51.692 --> 19:54.110
[Piano flourish]

19:54.144 --> 20:00.066
♪ Happy Birthday
to you ♪

20:00.100 --> 20:05.738
♪ Happy Birthday
to you ♪

20:05.772 --> 20:09.575
♪ Happy Birthday

20:09.609 --> 20:15.114
♪ Mr. director

20:15.132 --> 20:19.285
♪ Happy Birthday

20:19.319 --> 20:24.757
♪ to you

20:24.792 --> 20:31.463
thank you... Marilyn.

20:31.482 --> 20:33.232
[Applause]

20:35.552 --> 20:40.490
[Applause continues,
murmuring, calling out]

20:55.270 --> 20:56.987
I wonder if she
got Karen to coach her.

20:57.778 --> 20:59.746
Come on, you know
it's just a performance.

20:59.780 --> 21:02.499
He told you
he loved you.

21:02.533 --> 21:04.084
You still gonna go
visit your folks today?

21:04.118 --> 21:05.952
Ugh, don't think
I have a choice.

21:06.003 --> 21:08.171
I wasn't even going
to tell them I was in town,

21:08.205 --> 21:09.506
but my mom saw me

21:09.540 --> 21:11.091
in a publicity photo
in the <i>Globe.</i>

21:11.125 --> 21:12.959
Mm, they're so nice.

21:13.010 --> 21:14.177
Tom wants
to meet them.

21:14.211 --> 21:15.428
Oh, that'll be fun.

21:15.463 --> 21:17.881
[Mimicking]
That'll be fun.

21:17.915 --> 21:19.265
- [Giggles]
- I've never done this.

21:19.300 --> 21:20.850
Come on,
it's good for you.

21:20.885 --> 21:22.268
[Muffled]
That is good.

21:22.303 --> 21:23.486
I almost got you,
didn't I?

21:23.521 --> 21:24.804
You really did.

21:24.855 --> 21:26.022
Maybe you should
go get some cake.

21:26.057 --> 21:28.641
I think I should.

21:28.692 --> 21:30.527
[Louder, indistinct chatter]

21:30.561 --> 21:32.278
It's probably loaded.
Thank you.

21:32.280 --> 21:33.730
- Hi.
- Hey.

21:33.764 --> 21:36.032
...can I have a piece?
Sure, of course.

21:36.067 --> 21:37.200
- Here.
- Thank you.

21:37.234 --> 21:38.818
Here.

21:38.869 --> 21:40.570
Thanks for
standing in for me.

21:40.604 --> 21:43.323
But I think I'm gonna stand in
for myself from now on.

21:43.374 --> 21:47.494
- I need to get used to it.
- Yeah, fair enough.

21:47.545 --> 21:49.629
I appreciate you
coming over, Eileen,

21:49.663 --> 21:51.331
but my position
is unchanged.

21:51.382 --> 21:53.316
Tom
has agreed.

21:53.350 --> 21:54.918
He asked us
to talk you through this,

21:54.952 --> 21:57.587
but there's no time,
honestly.

21:57.621 --> 21:59.305
Well, that's on you.

21:59.340 --> 22:01.141
You're the one who kept
driving this forward

22:01.175 --> 22:03.176
faster than
it should've been.

22:03.227 --> 22:06.346
I'm very sensitive
to this situation, Julia.

22:06.397 --> 22:08.248
But ultimately,
it was your mistake.

22:08.282 --> 22:10.483
Now, I don't think
it's fair

22:10.518 --> 22:11.935
to keep an entire production
hostage over...

22:11.969 --> 22:13.686
I'm not holding
anyone hostage.

22:13.737 --> 22:15.438
I have millions
on the line.

22:15.472 --> 22:16.573
I have everything
on the line.

22:16.607 --> 22:18.158
- So do I!
- Eileen.

22:18.192 --> 22:20.860
Hi. What's, uh,
what's going on?

22:20.911 --> 22:23.997
Julia
will fill you in.

22:24.031 --> 22:25.615
- Honey?
- Mom?

22:25.649 --> 22:26.833
- Julia.
- It's fine.

22:26.867 --> 22:27.917
You guys, it's fine.

22:27.952 --> 22:30.537
I need
to talk to Tom.

22:30.588 --> 22:32.338
I promise you,
things are going to be fine.

22:32.373 --> 22:33.456
Just... where's my cell phone?

22:33.490 --> 22:36.492
- Julia?
- It's fine.

22:39.329 --> 22:42.298
[Playing
<i>the 20th Century Fox mambo]</i>

22:42.332 --> 22:46.069
♪

22:46.103 --> 22:50.640
♪ The 20th Century Fox
mambo ♪

22:50.674 --> 22:52.642
Thank you, everybody.

22:57.014 --> 22:58.565
Who is that?

22:58.616 --> 23:01.234
They call her
Marilyn Monroe.

23:01.285 --> 23:04.988
She's gorgeous.
I bet she's really gonna hit.

23:05.022 --> 23:06.372
Blondes are
a dime a dozen in this town.

23:06.407 --> 23:08.875
You're never gonna hear
from her again.

23:08.909 --> 23:10.243
I don't know,
I think she's...

23:10.294 --> 23:13.046
Okay, stop.
S... just please stop.

23:13.080 --> 23:15.331
- It's not terrible.
- Do not tell me

23:15.365 --> 23:16.332
it is not terrible.

23:16.366 --> 23:18.251
It is truly dreadful.

23:18.302 --> 23:20.837
Isn't my entrance yet?

23:20.871 --> 23:26.426
Rebecca,
how's that change coming?

23:26.477 --> 23:28.561
I never said
I was a writer.

23:28.596 --> 23:30.763
And Julia isn't here
to write it.

23:30.814 --> 23:33.266
By the way, now she's probably
never going to come.

23:33.317 --> 23:34.984
If we hire Michael, I don't
know what she's gonna do.

23:35.019 --> 23:36.736
There is no "if" about it.

23:36.770 --> 23:38.321
She's gonna have to suck it up
and be professional.

23:38.355 --> 23:40.940
We can't expect Rebecca to
rehearse without a leading man.

23:40.991 --> 23:42.775
And I am not doing
three weeks of previews

23:42.826 --> 23:44.744
without a book writer a lyricist.

23:44.778 --> 23:47.780
Rebecca...
Rebecca.

23:50.501 --> 23:52.001
What is going on?

23:52.036 --> 23:53.836
The evening gloves
are hard to get on and off

23:53.871 --> 23:55.338
when she's sweaty.

23:55.372 --> 23:56.789
Your leading lady
doesn't sweat, dear.

23:56.840 --> 24:00.343
She glows.
Karen, Ivy, get out here.

24:00.377 --> 24:02.879
Tom, I need
a longer button on <i>Mambo.</i>

24:02.913 --> 24:04.430
So what are we doing?

24:04.465 --> 24:06.799
Okay, during the extended
button of mambo,

24:06.850 --> 24:08.518
you two will stand
either side of her,

24:08.552 --> 24:12.188
take a glove each,
and remove it gently.

24:12.223 --> 24:16.142
Wait, we're taking
her gloves off for her?

24:16.193 --> 24:19.262
You heard me.
Do it.

24:28.155 --> 24:31.291
Dev?
What are you doing here?

24:31.325 --> 24:33.793
I, uh... I had something
I really had to do...

24:33.827 --> 24:35.995
Um, bring you flowers.

24:36.046 --> 24:38.331
- How much time do I have?
- None.

24:38.382 --> 24:41.167
That is so sweet.

24:41.218 --> 24:43.336
I mean, this is...
This is really, really sweet,

24:43.387 --> 24:44.837
but I'm working.
Why didn't you call?

24:44.888 --> 24:46.889
- Wanted to surprise you.
- I'm surprised.

24:46.924 --> 24:49.092
This actually
isn't a really good time.

24:49.126 --> 24:50.727
Oh, I don't mind waiting.

24:50.761 --> 24:52.095
- I can watch, can't I?
- Actually, you can't.

24:52.129 --> 24:53.813
There's all
these security things

24:53.847 --> 24:56.149
because of Rebecca,
but I'll see you at the room.

24:56.183 --> 24:57.984
I can't even watch?

24:58.018 --> 24:59.986
We're at the colonial lodge
on Stuart, room 139.

25:00.020 --> 25:01.404
I'll be there
around 8:00.

25:01.438 --> 25:04.490
Okay, let's take it
again, please.

25:04.525 --> 25:08.077
[Laughs]

25:08.112 --> 25:09.495
[Sighs]

25:09.530 --> 25:11.364
- How's the search coming?
- Julia...

25:11.415 --> 25:12.832
You know I love you
more than anything.

25:12.866 --> 25:14.584
So it's true.
You sold me out.

25:14.618 --> 25:18.254
- I did not sell you...
- Okay, I'm done.

25:18.289 --> 25:20.006
You tell them if he comes
to Boston, I'm out.

25:20.040 --> 25:21.874
I'm <i>out.</i>

25:31.313 --> 25:34.113
So, what are the options
if she quit?

25:34.677 --> 25:37.262
Well, we'd have to get
a new book writer,

25:37.313 --> 25:38.930
and Tom might quit.

25:38.981 --> 25:41.566
Then we'd have to get
a new composer.

25:41.600 --> 25:44.235
And pretty soon,

25:44.270 --> 25:47.088
it would all just be
a ridiculous waste of time,

25:47.123 --> 25:49.641
we'd be in courts,
and everybody would be right.

25:49.675 --> 25:51.443
Right about what?

25:51.477 --> 25:56.681
About me not being able
to do this by myself.

25:56.715 --> 26:02.504
Plus which, I wouldn't
expect you to stick around,

26:02.538 --> 26:07.175
given that your best friend
is our primary investor.

26:07.209 --> 26:10.011
Hey, it's just money.

26:10.045 --> 26:12.297
$7 million
is not "just money."

26:12.348 --> 26:15.300
Sure, it is.

26:15.351 --> 26:18.019
Now, you're gonna
have to go ahead

26:18.053 --> 26:21.139
and hire back Michael.
Let her make a decision.

26:21.190 --> 26:23.525
Your responsibility
is to the show, not to her,

26:23.559 --> 26:27.695
and right now,
the show needs Michael.

26:27.730 --> 26:29.898
But that's just what

26:29.932 --> 26:33.234
this know-nothing lowlife
of a barkeep knows.

26:33.268 --> 26:36.321
You know what?

26:36.372 --> 26:39.858
I have a thing
for know-nothing lowlifes.

26:39.892 --> 26:41.292
- Really?
- Mm.

26:41.327 --> 26:44.329
I heard that about you.

26:46.499 --> 26:48.133
You know...

26:48.167 --> 26:53.922
I don't have to go to Boston
till the morning...

26:53.956 --> 26:55.423
Technically.

26:55.458 --> 26:58.476
Oh, I'm closing up early.

26:58.511 --> 27:00.145
I'm calling
the casting director.

27:00.179 --> 27:02.347
Yeah, do it now,

27:02.398 --> 27:06.184
'cause there won't be
time later, I promise you.

27:07.636 --> 27:11.322
[Laughter]
So he went on in her corset.

27:11.357 --> 27:13.741
He was right.
It looked better on him.

27:13.776 --> 27:17.028
[Laughter]

27:17.079 --> 27:19.781
Uh, so, Ronald,
you own a paint store?

27:19.815 --> 27:23.251
Yep. 35 years.

27:23.285 --> 27:25.587
I was hoping to pass on
my business sense,

27:25.621 --> 27:27.455
but evidently not.

27:27.489 --> 27:29.374
Here we go.

27:29.425 --> 27:31.459
Paul here,
he's a doctor.

27:31.493 --> 27:34.262
That's a solid,
long-term profession.

27:34.296 --> 27:36.548
You know, dancing
is a profession as well.

27:36.599 --> 27:39.384
You don't see so many
60-year-old dancers.

27:39.435 --> 27:42.020
Ronnie.

27:42.054 --> 27:43.771
I'm sorry, Tom.

27:43.806 --> 27:46.858
We really do love theater
in this family.

27:46.892 --> 27:49.611
I take no offense.

27:49.645 --> 27:51.980
Actually, Ronald,
I agree.

27:52.014 --> 27:53.364
Both: - You do?
- I know a lot of dancers.

27:53.399 --> 27:55.400
I've seen
some real heartbreak.

27:55.451 --> 27:59.204
You're just one injury away
from financial disaster.

27:59.238 --> 28:00.955
I like this one.

28:00.990 --> 28:03.124
[Knock at door]

28:03.158 --> 28:05.159
Come in.

28:05.193 --> 28:07.078
[Background chatter]

28:07.129 --> 28:09.247
Oh, it's you.

28:09.298 --> 28:12.300
You're still here?

28:12.334 --> 28:15.303
Just wanted to make sure
you were okay.

28:15.337 --> 28:18.473
I'm getting there.

28:18.507 --> 28:22.310
Listen, I thought
of something else about Marilyn.

28:22.344 --> 28:24.846
What was that?

28:24.880 --> 28:27.815
She glowed
in the light.

28:27.850 --> 28:29.734
Some photographer
said it was 'cause

28:29.768 --> 28:31.236
she had lots of little hairs
on her body,

28:31.270 --> 28:34.822
but that's not it.

28:34.857 --> 28:39.277
She was luminous.

28:39.311 --> 28:41.329
[Whispering]
Like you.

28:42.948 --> 28:46.417
I can act, too.

28:46.452 --> 28:50.505
Oh, I know you can.

28:50.539 --> 28:54.842
You, my darling,
are a lovely little actress.

28:54.877 --> 28:58.379
Hmm.
Thank you.

29:00.415 --> 29:03.184
Why is it so damn difficult

29:03.218 --> 29:05.720
to get a simple compliment
from you?

29:05.754 --> 29:08.923
There you are.

29:12.027 --> 29:14.428
[Objects clatter,
thudding]

29:16.565 --> 29:18.650
Can I be of help?

29:18.701 --> 29:21.352
Yeah, you can
help me dry.

29:21.403 --> 29:22.654
Okay.

29:22.688 --> 29:25.907
Let me ask you
a question.

29:25.941 --> 29:28.192
What's the worst thing you've
ever seen happen to a dancer?

29:28.243 --> 29:30.244
Oh, God...

29:30.279 --> 29:33.331
I don't even want to say
what the worst thing is.

29:33.365 --> 29:36.084
Blown knees, bad back.

29:36.118 --> 29:39.370
Just... aging,
and then what do you do?

29:39.421 --> 29:41.956
You can bartend
or wait tables,

29:41.990 --> 29:45.009
but try retiring on that.

29:45.044 --> 29:46.761
Well, I hope you can talk
some sense into the boy,

29:46.795 --> 29:49.597
'cause God knows
he won't listen to me.

29:49.632 --> 29:52.050
I don't need anybody to talk
any sense into me, pop.

29:52.101 --> 29:53.801
Sam...

29:53.835 --> 29:55.470
Hey, you know, when you
and my father are done

29:55.504 --> 29:57.271
taking an axe
to my life choices,

29:57.306 --> 30:00.391
maybe you can give me
a ride back to the hotel.

30:05.064 --> 30:06.564
- Hey.
- Hey.

30:06.615 --> 30:07.815
It's kind of late.
What are you doing here?

30:07.849 --> 30:09.117
Oh, I'm looking
for Derek.

30:09.151 --> 30:10.785
We were supposed
to meet at the hotel.

30:10.819 --> 30:13.071
We're going out for dinner
for his birthday.

30:13.105 --> 30:14.656
You're not at your post.

30:14.690 --> 30:17.692
Oh, well, they sent me out
for a neti... pot.

30:22.998 --> 30:24.298
She is not
to be disturbed.

30:24.333 --> 30:25.667
I'm not looking
for her.

30:25.701 --> 30:27.251
Eellis, can you
handle this please?

30:27.302 --> 30:29.087
[Derek, low conversation,
Rebecca laughs]

30:29.138 --> 30:31.005
Come on.

30:31.040 --> 30:34.425
It's gonna be fine.

30:36.545 --> 30:40.598
[Rebecca giggling,
Derek, low chatter]

30:46.355 --> 30:48.072
This is nice.

30:48.107 --> 30:52.510
It's nice to finally get
some time together.

30:52.544 --> 30:54.462
- Yeah.
- Dev?

30:54.496 --> 30:55.997
You okay?

30:56.031 --> 30:57.548
Yeah, yeah,
I'm great.

30:59.518 --> 31:04.005
Okay, um, Karen...

31:04.039 --> 31:08.292
A lot's been happening
with me lately,

31:08.343 --> 31:12.046
and I've been thinking
about the future.

31:12.080 --> 31:15.600
- And I love you.
- I love you, too.

31:15.634 --> 31:19.220
But after everything
that's happened with me at work

31:19.254 --> 31:23.991
and you being out of town...

31:24.026 --> 31:26.811
I don't know
how to say this, so...

31:26.862 --> 31:29.647
I'll just say it.

31:29.681 --> 31:32.900
Karen...

31:32.934 --> 31:34.652
[Gasps]

31:34.703 --> 31:37.455
Will you marry me?

31:37.489 --> 31:40.024
[Gasps]
Marry you?

31:40.058 --> 31:42.794
Yeah, it's not
all that crazy, is it?

31:42.828 --> 31:46.547
No, of course not, I just...
I don't know what to say.

31:46.582 --> 31:49.700
Well, say yes.

31:49.735 --> 31:51.135
I'm in Tech.

31:51.170 --> 31:53.721
Is that the same thing
as a yes?

31:53.756 --> 31:55.473
I'm so sorry, Dev.

31:55.507 --> 31:57.809
I'm just under so much pressure.
Tech is so crazy...

31:57.843 --> 31:59.494
That's sounding
more and more like a no.

31:59.528 --> 32:00.895
No, it's not
a yes or a no.

32:00.929 --> 32:01.929
It's "I'm in Tech."

32:01.964 --> 32:03.514
Dev, I'm serious.

32:03.565 --> 32:06.517
Yeah, I can see
you're serious.

32:06.568 --> 32:08.569
I see that very plainly.

32:08.604 --> 32:11.689
[Whispered]
Oh, my God, I...

32:11.740 --> 32:14.275
God, I'm sorry.

32:14.309 --> 32:16.611
I'm sorry.

32:30.549 --> 32:32.219
I'm sorry.

32:32.427 --> 32:33.644
For what?

32:33.678 --> 32:35.529
I didn't mean
to take sides.

32:35.563 --> 32:37.466
Sure, you did.

32:38.700 --> 32:42.803
