Maybe your dad is right.

32:42.837 --> 32:44.738
Maybe you could start
a retirement fund.

32:44.772 --> 32:46.040
A retirement...

32:46.074 --> 32:47.992
You planning on
giving me a raise now?

32:48.043 --> 32:51.362
- If it was up to me...
- None of it is up to you.

32:51.396 --> 32:52.746
Or my dad.

32:52.780 --> 32:54.298
Tom, do you honestly think

32:54.332 --> 32:55.966
I have never thought
about all of this before?

32:56.001 --> 32:59.970
I made a decision to do
what I love to do,

33:00.005 --> 33:02.756
and I accept everything
that comes along with that.

33:02.790 --> 33:04.725
Whatever happens next,
I accept it.

33:04.759 --> 33:06.560
This is what theater is.

33:06.594 --> 33:11.649
It is joy one day,
and it's gone the next.

33:11.683 --> 33:13.150
It's like a religion,

33:13.184 --> 33:15.269
and I don't apologize

33:15.303 --> 33:18.038
for wanting to be
a part of that,

33:18.073 --> 33:20.941
and I don't wish
for something more.

33:20.975 --> 33:24.745
I really don't.

33:35.490 --> 33:40.427
You are...

33:40.462 --> 33:42.496
My best self.

33:45.934 --> 33:47.935
[Door opens]

33:47.969 --> 33:49.636
Oh, Lord!

33:49.670 --> 33:51.355
Two boys kissing!

33:51.389 --> 33:53.140
Paul strickland,
what's the matter with you?

33:53.174 --> 33:55.559
- He's like a child.
- Get a room.

33:55.610 --> 33:57.061
Not here, though.
Not this... not here.

33:57.112 --> 34:00.030
- [Giggles]
- Unbelievable.

34:00.065 --> 34:01.398
[Laughter]

34:01.433 --> 34:04.401
[Pop music]

34:04.452 --> 34:06.153
